		#react-masked-field             
			%article.jumbotron
				.container
					.row.project-name.text-center
						%h1 React-Masked-Field
						%p A masked input component built in React.js
		%article.container
			.row
				.col-sm-10.col-sm-offset-1
					.project-description
						%h3 About React-Masked-Field
						%p The MaskedField component is a text input field that allows you to restrict and format the values that can be entered into it, while informing the user of the expected input. Common uses include dates, phone numbers, social security numbers and tax IDs.
					.project-box
						%ul.nav.project-nav
							%li#demo.tab
								%a Demo
							%li#installation.tab 
								%a Installation
							%li#example.tab 
								%a Example 
							%li#props.tab 
								%a Props
						#project-demo.project-detail
							%h4 Demo
							%p The example below will only allow a numeric entry for dates.
							%form
								.form-group
									%label date
									.react-masked-field-demo
						#project-installation.project-detail.hidden
							%h4 Installation
							%p A standalone build is also available in the dist folder.
							%code
								npm install react-masked-field
						#project-example.project-detail.hidden
							%h4 Example
							%p 
								%code
									%span.variable 
										var 
									MaskedField = 
									%span.method
										require
									('react-masked-field');
							%p 
								%code                 
									%span.variable
										function 
									handleComplete(date) {
									%br/
									%span.method
										&nbsp; console.log
									('Date is ' + date);
									%br/
									} 
							%p 
								%code
									React.render(
									%br/
									&nbsp; &lt;MaskedField mask="99/99/9999" onComplete={handleComplete} /&gt;,
									%br/
									%span.method
										&nbsp; document.getElementById
									('demo')
									%br/
									);              
						#project-props.project-detail.hidden
							%h4 Props
							.form-group
								%label mask
								.code-group
									%code 
										string 
										%span.attribute
											optional                
								%p The mask applied to the value of the field. For each character of the mask that matches a translation, the input character will be restricted to the corresponding regular expression. If no mask is provided, it will function like a normal input element.
							.form-group         
								%label format
								.code-group
									%code 
										string 
										%span.attribute
											optional
									%br/    
									%code 
										default
										%span.method
											'_'             
								%p The placeholder used for characters that haven't yet been filled in (.e.g MM/DD/YYYY for a date field). The format string should have a length of 1 or match the length of the mask.
							.form-group                   
								%label translations
								.code-group
									%code 
										object
										%span.attribute
											optional
									%br/    
									%code 
										default   
										%br/
										%span.method 
											{
										%br/	
										%span.method 	
											&#39;9&#39;: /\d/, 
										%br/
										%span.method 
											&#39;a&#39;: /[A-Za-z]/,
										%br/
										%span.method 
											&#39;*&#39;: /[A-Za-z0-9]/
										%br/
										%span.method 	
											}										
								%p Additional (or overridden) translations for converting mask characters to regular expressions.
							.form-group                   
								%label onComplete
								.code-group
									%code 
										function
										%span.attribute
											optional                
								%p The onComplete event is triggered when the mask has been completely filled. The value of the field is passed to the event handler.

